## Onboarding Checklist

The intended readership of this page is new joiners to the team and the hiring Manager, the page illustrates Checklist to follow smooth Onboarding of new joiners to this Team.

#### Step - 1 (Line Manager)

Request following items:

- Developer laptop 

- User account(@justice.gov.uk)

- Admin account(@justiceuk.onmicrosoft.com)

- Gmail account(@digital.justice.gov.uk)

#### Step - 2 (Line Manager)

- Send instrcutions on how to obtain password from support desk via personal email before the start date.

- Arrange a call to kickoff onboarding process with the new joiner on the start date

#### Step - 3 (New joiner)

- Install WSL from windows apps store and other list of tools as detailed [here](https://ministryofjustice.github.io/nvvs-devops/documentation/team-guide/team-tools.html#team-tools)

#### Step - 4 (New joiner)

- Follow README on this [repo](https://github.com/smjmoj/provision-ubuntu2004-on-wsl2)(this is a draft repository once finalised will update the link)

#### Step - 5 (New joiner)

- Configure AWS Vault as detailed [here](https://ministryofjustice.github.io/nvvs-devops/documentation/team-guide/best-practices/use-aws-sso.html#finally-update-the-config-file)

#### Step - 6 (New joiner)

- Request access to the following:

- Github

- Zenhub

- NACs Admin

- DNS DHCP Admin

- Slack Channel 

- Service Now

- Confluence

- PasswordManager (1Password)
